{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 11 introduces new features for finding and fixing bugs fast. Discover how to simulate network conditions and thermal states, and how to override your app’s runtime environment while debugging. See how the debugging features work with Xcode previews to identify issues before Build & Run. Learn how to work with the View Debugger to troubleshoot your SwiftUI views."}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-412-Debugging-in-Xcode-11","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"title":"Debugging in Xcode 11","roleHeading":"WWDC19","role":"sampleCode"},"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc19\/412","overridingTitle":"Watch Video (37 min)"}},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-412-debugging-in-xcode-11"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"Thermal-State-Condition","level":2,"text":"Thermal State Condition"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"can set one of the following: fair, serious, critical."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"lets us analyze our app behavior in these states.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The device does ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"not","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" actually get warmer.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Useful if we observe and behave differently when we have different thermal states.","type":"text"}]}