ility Options"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can use them both while Debugging the simulator or while debugging a SwiftUI live view.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"New-Run-Time-Issue-Breakpoint","level":2,"text":"New Run Time Issue Breakpoint"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC19-412-run","type":"image"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Debugging-SwiftUI-Live-Previews","level":2,"text":"Debugging SwiftUI Live Previews"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Control"},{"type":"text","text":"+"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"click"},{"type":"text","text":" on the play button to choose to debug a preview, then it behaves like a normal debug session."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Do not change the window where the previewed view is, or the debugging session will disappear instantly.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC19-412-swiftUI"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"##￼SwiftUI Runtime Issues"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Equivalent to auto layout issues or when we try to change our UI from a background thread, they point out issues of our SwiftUI usage.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"These are shown even when debugging SwiftUI Live Previews, in fact the live preview is a mini-app where we only focus on that view.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(Every change ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"builds","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"runs"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" that view, it’s not really “live”)","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can also refresh a SwiftUI preview via 